name: glutamine synthetase
reaction: ATP + L-glutamate + NH3 = ADP + phosphate + L-glutamine [RN:R00253]
comment: Glutamine synthetase, which catalyses the incorporation of ammonium into glutamate, is a key enzyme of nitrogen metabolism found in all domains of life. Several types have been described, differing in their oligomeric structures and cofactor requirements.
